-44; Deng, T., Dong, J., Wang, Y., Variation of terrestrial ecosystem recorded by stable carbon isotopes of fossils in northern China during the Quatenary (2002) Chin. Sci. Bull., 47, pp. 76-77; Deng, T., Xue, X., Dong, J., The evidence of fossil carbon isotopes of the climatic event at the beginning of Quaternary (1999) Chin. Sci. Bull., 44, pp. 477-480; Ding, Z., Yang, S., C3/C4 vegetation evolution over the last 7.0 Myr in the Chinese Loess Plateau: Evidence from pedogenic carbonate δ13C (2000) Palaeogeogr. Palaeoclimatol. Palaeoecol., 160, pp. 291-299; Kutzbach, J., Prell, W., Ruddiman, W., Sensitivity of Eurasian climate to surface uplift of the Tibetan Plateau (1993) J. Geol., 101, pp. 177-190; Yin, L., Li, M., A study of the geographic distribution and ecology of C4 plants in China: I. C4 plant distribution in China and their relation with regional climatic condition (1997) Acta Ecol. Sin., 17, pp. 350-363; Liu, X., Yin, A., Sensitivity of East Asia monsoon climate to the uplift of the Tibetan Plateau (2002) Palaeogeogr. Palaeoclimatol. Palaeoecol., 183, pp. 223-245; Ren, X., (1981) Geological and Ecological Studies of Qinghai-Xizang (Tibet) Plateau, 1, pp. 139-143; Chen, W., Pliocene environment of Hipparion Fauna of Middle Himalaya Range (1982) Vertebrata Palasiatica, 20, pp. 45-54; Zheng, H., Powell, C., An, Z., Zhou, J., Dong, G., Pliocene uplift of the northern Tibetan Plateau (2000) Geology, 28, pp. 715-718; Harrison, T.M., Copeland, P., Kidd, W.S.F., Yin, A., Raising Tibet (1992) Science, 255, pp. 1663-1670; Molnar, P., England, P., Martinod, J., Mantle dynamics, uplift of the Tibetan Plateau, and the Indian monsoon (1993) Rev. Geophys., 31, pp. 357-396; Prell, W., Kutzbach, J., Sensitivity of the Indian monsoon to forcing parameters and implications for its evolution (1992) Nature, 360, pp. 647-652; Burkle, L., Distribution of diatoms in the northern Indian Ocean: Relationship to physical oceanography (1989) Mar. Micropaleontol., 15, pp. 53-65; Rea, D